Its unfortunate that this place is led by such an unprofessional, ill-mannered owner.  I was excited to try this restaurant for my birthday, since it’s one of the few Korean BBQ’s located close to Chinatown. Unfortunately, immediately walking into the restaurant with my group of 10 including my family and friends, we were met with a rude lady who pushed my family and I quickly to the side, saying that she was trying to “serve other customers” and that we had to make way. I called her out, saying that she was being rude and impolite to my family, but she dismissed my remark and made a nasty face at me instead.  I had made a reservation for my group, and we were subsequently seated, but the same lady was the one who started to serve our table. While getting the table set-up, she made it obvious to our group that she was unhappy to be serving us. “Move, Im trying to set up!” was yelled by her. Her tone was sullen and she continued to sulk at us, rudely telling my family members to move to the side when setting up our grill.  Further, when asking her if we could be served water, she obviously ignored us and continued to walk away with a sour look. We later learned that this lady was the OWNER. I was surprised and disappointed at how someone who calls herself the owner can act so unprofessional and incompetent.  Ultimately, we had decided to stay despite our encounter with the owner, since I was craving Korean BBQ and wasn’t going to let her ruin my birthday. Fortunately, our waiters and waitresses were kind and tactful to our requests, unlike the leadership of this restaurant. We had ordered the large pork combo (seared pork belly, pork jowl, pork collar) and large beef combo (boneless short rib, thinly sliced brisket, prime rib eye). We had also ordered a couple beers.  I had personally thanked our waitress, telling her that I was grateful for her being so kind to us and that the owner’s treatment of our large group was unacceptable and that restaurant owners should be role models of service and not disreputable. Despite us giving her our business (spent over ~$450), the owner continued to ignore our table and avoided eye contact with my family and I throughout our whole time there.  The food was delicious, but its unfortunate that its owned by someone so immature and unprincipled. I will NEVER support, promote, or perform business with this restaurant ever again thanks to her, and I hope that no one else has to ever experience such service from leadership. Thanks for ruining my birthday.
